==Finnish==
===Noun===

'''hitto''' (plural ''hitot'')

''(mild expletive)'' Hell, fuck, heck, or shit. Somewhat comparable to Geezers!

Finnish synonyms: [[helvetti]], [[halvattu]]

===Usage notes===

''Hitto'' is never used as an object in an imperative sentence, unlike [[helvetti]] or [[vittu]]. Doing that would sound lame. Therefore, you can say ''mene helvettiin'' or ''painu vittuun'' to tell someone to get lost, but you can't say ''mene hittoon''. However, you can ask ''Mihin hittoon se tyyppi meni?'' (Where the hell did that guy go?) or ''Mistä hitosta sä ton löysit?'' (Where the hell did you find that?).

===Etymology===

Probably, but not necessarily, derived from Swedish ''hitåt'' which sounds like "Out of here!"

